    <briefdescription>
<para>A configurable sequence of complete <computeroutput><ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1_color" kindref="compound">Color</ref></computeroutput> values with run-length style counts. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Each effective position in the sequence yields one full foreground/background color pair. The sequence can be accessed by cyclic index or by a normalized value in the range <computeroutput>0.0..1.0</computeroutput>. Consumers may perform multiple lookups, for example to combine the foreground of one entry with the background of a neighboring entry. <simplesect kind="par"><title>Tested:</title><para><computeroutput>ColorSequenceTest</computeroutput> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
